  blockquote
    p
      span.i18n-fsf-quote
        | &ldquo;Free software&rdquo; means software that respects users&rsquo; freedom and community. Roughly, <strong>the users have the freedom to run, copy, distribute, study, change and improve the software</strong>. With these freedoms, the users (both individually and collectively) control the program and what it does for them.
        a href='https://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html'
